fields.name: Barbell Bench Press
fields.description: The barbell bench press is a compound exercise that primarily targets the chest muscles, along with the shoulders and triceps. Keep your feet flat on the ground and lower the bar to your mid-chest, then press it back up while keeping your elbows slightly tucked. Avoid arching your back excessively to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
fields.description: The Incline Barbell Bench Press targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Lie on an incline bench, grip the bar slightly wider than shoulder-width, and press it upward until your arms are fully extended. Avoid arching your back excessively to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
fields.description: The decline barbell bench press targets the lower part of the chest, along with the triceps and shoulders. Keep your feet secured and lower the barbell to your lower chest, then press it back up in a controlled motion. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
fields.description: The Dumbbell Bench Press is an upper body exercise that primarily targets the chest muscles, along with the shoulders and triceps. Keep your feet flat on the ground, back pressed into the bench, and lower the dumbbells slowly until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press
fields.description: The incline dumbbell bench press targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your back pressed against the bench and press the dumbbells up in a controlled motion. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to reduce shoulder strain.

fields.name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press
fields.description: The decline dumbbell bench press targets the lower chest muscles, along with the triceps and shoulders. Keep your back pressed against the bench and lower the dumbbells slowly until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Dumbbell Flyes
fields.description: Dumbbell Flyes target the chest muscles, specifically the pectorals. Keep a slight bend in your elbows as you lower the weights out to the sides, then bring them back together above your chest. Avoid letting your elbows drop too low to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Incline Dumbbell Flyes
fields.description: Incline Dumbbell Flyes target the upper chest muscles by opening and closing the arms in a wide arc. Keep a slight bend in your elbows and control the movement to avoid straining your shoulders. Avoid letting the dumbbells touch at the top to maintain tension on the chest.

fields.name: Cable Crossovers
fields.description: Cable crossovers are an isolation exercise targeting the chest muscles. Stand between two cable machines, grab the handles, and pull them together in front of your body with a slight bend in your elbows. Avoid swinging your arms or using momentum to ensure maximum chest engagement.

fields.name: Low Cable Crossovers
fields.description: Perform cable crossover with pulleys set low to target upper chest.

fields.name: Machine Chest Press
fields.description: The machine chest press is an exercise targeting the chest muscles, specifically the pectorals, with assistance from the shoulders and triceps. Keep your back flat against the pad and press the handles forward until your arms are fully extended. Avoid locking your elbows to maintain tension on the muscles.

fields.name: Pec Deck Machine
fields.description: The Pec Deck Machine targets the chest muscles, specifically the pectorals. Sit with your back firmly against the pad and bring the handles together in front of you, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. Avoid letting your elbows drop too low to maintain tension on the chest.

fields.name: Push-Ups
fields.description: Push-ups are a bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, lowering your chest to just above the ground. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Decline Push-Ups
fields.description: Decline push-ups are a variation of the standard push-up that targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Place your feet on an elevated surface and your hands on the ground, maintaining a straight line from head to heels as you lower your chest. Avoid letting your hips sag to ensure proper form and reduce strain on your lower back.

fields.name: Diamond Push-Ups
fields.description: Diamond push-ups are a bodyweight exercise that primarily targets the chest, triceps, and shoulders. Position your hands close together under your chest, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers, and keep your elbows close to your body as you lower down. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent unnecessary shoulder strain.

fields.name: Barbell Deadlift
fields.description: The barbell deadlift is a compound exercise that primarily targets the back, along with the glutes, hamstrings, and core. Keep your back straight and engage your core as you lift the barbell from the ground by driving through your heels. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Conventional Deadlift
fields.description: The conventional deadlift is a compound exercise targeting the back, glutes, hamstrings, and core. Keep your back straight and engage your core as you lift the barbell from the ground by driving through your heels. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Sumo Deadlift
fields.description: The Sumo Deadlift is a lower body exercise that primarily targets the back, glutes, and hamstrings. Stand with a wide stance, toes slightly pointed out, and grip the barbell with your hands inside your knees, keeping your chest up as you lift. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Romanian Deadlift
fields.description: The Romanian Deadlift is a strength exercise targeting the back, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while lowering the barbell, maintaining a slight bend in your knees. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Barbell Bent-Over Row
fields.description: The Barbell Bent-Over Row is a strength exercise that targets the back muscles, including the lats, rhomboids, and traps. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while pulling the barbell towards your lower ribcage. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Dumbbell Bent-Over Row
fields.description: The Dumbbell Bent-Over Row targets the muscles in your upper and middle back, including the lats and rhomboids. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while pulling the dumbbells towards your waist. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: T-Bar Row
fields.description: The T-Bar Row is a back exercise that targets the middle back, lats, and rhomboids. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while pulling the bar towards your chest. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Seated Cable Row
fields.description: The seated cable row is an exercise that targets the muscles of the back, including the lats, rhomboids, and traps. Sit with your feet on the platform, knees slightly bent, and pull the handle towards your torso while keeping your back straight and chest up. Avoid rounding your shoulders forward to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Row
fields.description: The Single-Arm Dumbbell Row targets the back muscles, particularly the lats and rhomboids. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while pulling the dumbbell towards your hip. Avoid twisting your torso to ensure the back muscles do the work.

fields.name: Lat Pulldown (Wide Grip)
fields.description: The Lat Pulldown (Wide Grip) targets the latissimus dorsi, along with the upper back and shoulders. Sit with your thighs under the pad, grip the bar wider than shoulder-width, and pull it down to your chest while keeping your back straight. Avoid leaning back excessively to ensure the focus remains on your lats.

fields.name: Lat Pulldown (Close Grip)
fields.description: The Lat Pulldown (Close Grip) targets the back muscles, specifically the latissimus dorsi, with additional engagement of the biceps and forearms. Sit with your knees secured under the pad, grasp the close grip handle, and pull it down towards your chest while keeping your elbows close to your body. Avoid leaning back excessively to ensure proper back engagement.

fields.name: Pull-Ups
fields.description: Grip bar overhand shoulder-width, pull chest to bar, control descent.

fields.name: Chin-Ups
fields.description: Chin-ups are a bodyweight exercise targeting the back, biceps, and shoulders. Grip the bar with palms facing you, pull your chest towards the bar, and keep your core engaged. Avoid swinging your body to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Assisted Pull-Ups
fields.description: Assisted pull-ups are a back exercise that helps build strength by using a machine or band to reduce the weight you lift. Keep your core engaged and pull your chest towards the bar, leading with your elbows. Avoid swinging your body to ensure proper form.

fields.name: Straight-Arm Pulldown
fields.description: The straight-arm pulldown targets the lats and helps build a strong back. Keep your arms straight as you pull the bar down to your thighs, engaging your core throughout. Avoid bending your elbows to ensure maximum lat activation.

fields.name: Machine Row
fields.description: The machine row targets the muscles of the upper and middle back, including the latissimus dorsi and rhomboids. Keep your chest pressed against the pad and pull the handles towards you, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Hyperextensions
fields.description: Hyperextensions target the lower back, glutes, and hamstrings. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips to lower your torso, then lift back up in a controlled motion. Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Good Mornings
fields.description: Good Mornings are a back exercise that primarily targets the lower back, glutes, and hamstrings. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while maintaining a slight bend in the knees. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Barbell Overhead Press
fields.description: The Barbell Overhead Press is a strength exercise targeting the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a tight core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Seated Dumbbell Shoulder Press
fields.description: Seated with back support, press dumbbells from shoulders to overhead.

fields.name: Arnold Press
fields.description: The Arnold Press is a shoulder exercise that targets the deltoids, with added engagement of the triceps and upper chest. Start with dumbbells at shoulder height, palms facing you, then rotate your palms outward as you press overhead. Avoid arching your back by keeping your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raises
fields.description: Dumbbell Lateral Raises target the shoulder muscles, specifically the lateral deltoids. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a dumbbell in each hand, and lift your arms to the side until they are parallel to the floor. Avoid swinging your body or using momentum to lift the weights.

fields.name: Cable Lateral Raises
fields.description: Cable lateral raises target the shoulder muscles, specifically the lateral deltoids. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the cable handle with one hand, and lift your arm out to the side until it's parallel to the floor. Avoid using momentum; keep the movement controlled and focus on the shoulder muscles.

fields.name: Front Dumbbell Raises
fields.description: Front Dumbbell Raises target the front deltoids in your shoulders. Keep your core engaged and lift the dumbbells to shoulder height with controlled movements. Avoid swinging your arms to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Barbell Front Raise
fields.description: The barbell front raise targets the front deltoids in the shoulders. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the barbell with palms facing down, and lift it to shoulder height with controlled motion. Avoid swinging the barbell to maintain tension on the shoulders.

fields.name: Rear Delt Flyes (Bent-Over)
fields.description: Rear Delt Flyes (Bent-Over) target the rear deltoids and upper back muscles. Keep your back flat and hinge at the hips while lifting the weights out to the sides with a slight bend in the elbows. Avoid swinging the weights; focus on controlled movements.

fields.name: Reverse Pec Deck
fields.description: The Reverse Pec Deck targets the rear deltoids and upper back muscles. Sit facing the machine, grip the handles, and pull them back in a controlled motion while keeping your elbows slightly bent. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to maintain focus on the target muscles.

fields.name: Face Pulls
fields.description: Face Pulls target the rear deltoids, upper back, and shoulder stabilizers. Pull the rope towards your face with elbows high, keeping your shoulders down and back. Avoid using your lower back to generate momentum.

fields.name: Upright Rows
fields.description: Upright rows target the shoulders, particularly the deltoids, and also engage the trapezius muscles. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a barbell or dumbbells with an overhand grip, and lift them vertically to chest height, keeping elbows higher than wrists. Avoid using momentum or swinging the weights to ensure proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Barbell Shrugs
fields.description: Barbell Shrugs target the trapezius muscles in your shoulders. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the barbell with an overhand grip, and lift your shoulders straight up towards your ears. Avoid rolling your shoulders to prevent unnecessary strain.

fields.name: Dumbbell Shrugs
fields.description: Dumbbell shrugs target the trapezius muscles in your shoulders. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a dumbbell in each hand, and lift your shoulders straight up towards your ears. Avoid rolling your shoulders to prevent unnecessary strain.

fields.name: Machine Shoulder Press
fields.description: The machine shoulder press targets the shoulder muscles, specifically the deltoids. Sit with your back against the pad, grip the handles, and press upward without locking your elbows. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Landmine Press
fields.description: The Landmine Press is a shoulder exercise that also engages the triceps and core. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the end of the barbell with one hand, and press it upward while keeping your core tight. Avoid leaning back as you press to protect your lower back.

fields.name: Barbell Bicep Curl
fields.description: The barbell bicep curl is an exercise that targets the biceps in your arms. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the barbell with palms facing up, and curl it towards your chest while keeping elbows close to your body. Avoid swinging your body or using momentum to lift the weight.

fields.name: EZ-Bar Curl
fields.description: The EZ-Bar Curl is an arm exercise that primarily targets the biceps. Grip the EZ-bar with an underhand grip, keeping your elbows close to your torso, and curl the bar up towards your shoulders. Avoid swinging your body to maintain focus on the biceps.

fields.name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl
fields.description: The Dumbbell Bicep Curl is an arm exercise that primarily targets the biceps. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a dumbbell in each hand, and curl the weights towards your shoulders while keeping your elbows close to your body. Avoid swinging your arms or using momentum to lift the weights.

fields.name: Hammer Curls
fields.description: Neutral grip dumbbell curls targeting brachialis and brachioradialis.

fields.name: Incline Dumbbell Curl
fields.description: The incline dumbbell curl targets the biceps by performing curls on an inclined bench. Keep your back firmly against the bench and let your arms hang straight down before curling the weights up. Avoid swinging your arms to maintain focus on the biceps.

fields.name: Preacher Curl (Barbell)
fields.description: The preacher curl with a barbell targets the biceps, focusing on isolating the muscle for maximum growth. Keep your upper arms firmly against the preacher bench pad and curl the barbell up smoothly. Avoid lifting your elbows off the pad to prevent using momentum instead of muscle.

fields.name: Preacher Curl (Dumbbell)
fields.description: The preacher curl with dumbbells targets the biceps by isolating the muscle for maximum engagement. Sit on a preacher bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders. Avoid lifting your elbows off the pad to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Concentration Curl
fields.description: The concentration curl is an isolation exercise targeting the biceps. Sit on a bench with your feet flat, lean forward slightly, and curl a dumbbell with one arm, keeping your elbow against your inner thigh. Avoid swinging the weight and focus on a controlled movement.

fields.name: Cable Bicep Curl
fields.description: The cable bicep curl is an arm exercise that primarily targets the biceps. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the cable handle with palms facing up, and curl the handle towards your shoulders while keeping elbows close to your body. Avoid swinging your body or using momentum to lift the weight.

fields.name: Spider Curls
fields.description: Spider curls are an isolation exercise targeting the biceps. Perform them by lying face down on an incline bench, letting your arms hang straight down, and curling the weights up towards your shoulders. Avoid swinging your arms to maintain tension on the biceps throughout the movement.

fields.name: Reverse Curl
fields.description: The reverse curl is an arm exercise that primarily targets the biceps and forearms. Keep your palms facing down as you curl the weights towards your shoulders. Avoid swinging your arms or using momentum to ensure proper muscle engagement.

fields.name: Zottman Curls
fields.description: Zottman Curls are an arm exercise that targets the biceps and forearms. Start with a standard curl, then rotate your wrists to face downward as you lower the weights. Avoid swinging your arms to maintain control and maximize muscle engagement.

fields.name: Close-Grip Bench Press
fields.description: The close-grip bench press targets the triceps, with secondary activation of the chest and shoulders. Keep your hands shoulder-width apart on the bar to emphasize tricep engagement. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Skull Crushers (EZ-Bar)
fields.description: Skull Crushers with an EZ-Bar target the triceps. Lie on a bench, grip the EZ-Bar with hands shoulder-width apart, and lower it towards your forehead by bending your elbows. Avoid flaring your elbows out to maintain focus on the triceps.

fields.name: Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell)
fields.description: The Overhead Tricep Extension with a dumbbell targets the triceps in your arms. Keep your elbows close to your head and extend the dumbbell upwards, fully straightening your arms. Avoid flaring your elbows out to maintain proper form and focus on the triceps.

fields.name: Overhead Tricep Extension (Cable)
fields.description: Cable overhead extension with rope attachment.

fields.name: Tricep Pushdown (Rope)
fields.description: The Tricep Pushdown (Rope) targets the triceps muscles in your arms. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the rope with both hands, and extend your arms down while keeping your elbows close to your body. Avoid flaring your elbows out to ensure maximum tricep engagement.

fields.name: Tricep Pushdown (V-Bar)
fields.description: The Tricep Pushdown with a V-Bar targets the triceps, helping to build arm strength and definition. Keep your elbows close to your sides and push the bar down until your arms are fully extended. Avoid using your shoulders or back to assist in the movement; focus on isolating the triceps.

fields.name: Tricep Pushdown (Straight Bar)
fields.description: The Tricep Pushdown with a straight bar targets the triceps, helping to build arm strength and definition. Keep your elbows close to your sides and push the bar down until your arms are fully extended. Avoid using your shoulders or back to assist in the movement.

fields.name: Tricep Dips
fields.description: Tricep Dips are an effective bodyweight exercise targeting the triceps, shoulders, and chest. Keep your elbows close to your body as you lower and push through your palms to return to the starting position. Avoid letting your shoulders hunch forward to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Bench Dips
fields.description: Bench dips target the triceps, shoulders, and chest. Keep your back close to the bench and lower your body until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Tricep Diamond Push-Ups
fields.description: Tricep Diamond Push-Ups target the triceps, chest, and shoulders. Place your hands close together under your chest, forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers, and keep your elbows close to your body as you lower down. Avoid flaring your elbows out to maintain focus on the triceps.

fields.name: Tricep Kickbacks
fields.description: Tricep Kickbacks target the triceps, helping to build strength and definition in the back of your arms. Keep your upper arm stationary and hinge only at the elbow to extend your forearm behind you. Avoid swinging your arm or using momentum to ensure proper muscle engagement.

fields.name: Cable Overhead Tricep Extension
fields.description: The Cable Overhead Tricep Extension targets the triceps by extending the arms overhead using a cable machine. Keep your elbows close to your head and extend your arms fully without locking the elbows. Avoid flaring your elbows out to maintain proper form and maximize tricep engagement.

fields.name: Barbell Back Squat
fields.description: The barbell back squat is a compound exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and lower back. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower your hips back and down, ensuring your knees track over your toes. Avoid letting your heels lift off the ground to maintain balance and stability.

fields.name: Barbell Front Squat
fields.description: The barbell front squat is a compound exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and elbows high as you descend to maintain balance and proper form. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to prevent strain and ensure effective muscle engagement.

fields.name: Goblet Squat
fields.description: The goblet squat is a lower-body exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Hold a dumbbell or kettlebell close to your chest, keep your chest up, and squat down by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat.

fields.name: Leg Press
fields.description: The leg press is a strength exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Sit on the machine with your back flat against the pad and push the platform away with your feet shoulder-width apart. Avoid locking your knees at the top to prevent injury.

fields.name: Hack Squat
fields.description: The hack squat is a leg exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps, with secondary engagement of the hamstrings and glutes. Keep your back flat against the pad and your feet shoulder-width apart as you lower into the squat. Avoid locking your knees at the top to maintain tension on the muscles.

fields.name: Bulgarian Split Squat
fields.description: The Bulgarian Split Squat is a lower body exercise targeting the quads, glutes, and hamstrings. Stand a few feet in front of a bench, place one foot behind you on the bench, and lower your hips until your front thigh is parallel to the ground. Avoid letting your front knee extend past your toes to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Walking Lunges
fields.description: Walking lunges are a dynamic leg exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Step forward with one leg, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle, then push through the front heel to step forward with the other leg. Avoid letting your front knee extend past your toes to protect your joints.

fields.name: Stationary Lunges
fields.description: Stationary lunges are a lower body exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Step one foot forward and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about 90 degrees, keeping your front knee aligned with your ankle. Avoid letting your front knee extend past your toes to prevent strain.

fields.name: Reverse Lunges
fields.description: Reverse lunges are a lower body exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Step one foot back, lower your hips until both knees are bent at about 90 degrees, then return to standing. Avoid letting your front knee extend past your toes to protect your joints.

fields.name: Leg Extension Machine
fields.description: The leg extension machine targets the quadriceps muscles in the front of your thighs. Sit with your back against the pad, adjust the machine so your knees align with the pivot point, and extend your legs fully without locking your knees. Avoid using momentum; control the movement to maximize muscle engagement.

fields.name: Sissy Squats
fields.description: Sissy squats are a bodyweight exercise that targets the quadriceps, with secondary engagement of the core and hip flexors. Keep your torso upright and lean back as you bend your knees, lowering your body while keeping your heels elevated. Avoid letting your knees collapse inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Step-Ups
fields.description: Step-ups are a lower body exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Step onto a sturdy platform with one foot, driving through the heel to lift your body up, then step back down. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements for maximum benefit.

fields.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift
fields.description: The stiff-leg deadlift targets the hamstrings, glutes, and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while lowering the barbell, maintaining a slight bend in the knees. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Lying Leg Curl
fields.description: The lying leg curl targets the hamstrings at the back of your thighs. Lie face down on the machine, position your ankles under the padded lever, and curl your legs towards your glutes. Avoid lifting your hips off the bench to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Seated Leg Curl
fields.description: The seated leg curl targets the hamstrings, located at the back of your thighs. Sit with your back against the pad, adjust the machine to fit your legs, and curl your legs down by bending your knees. Avoid lifting your hips off the seat to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Standing Leg Curl
fields.description: The standing leg curl targets the hamstrings and glutes. Stand upright, hold onto a support, and curl one leg up towards your glutes, keeping your knees aligned. Avoid swinging your leg; focus on controlled movement.

fields.name: Nordic Hamstring Curl
fields.description: The Nordic Hamstring Curl is a bodyweight exercise targeting the hamstrings, glutes, and calves. Start by kneeling with your feet secured and slowly lower your torso forward, keeping your body straight from head to knees. Avoid bending at the hips to ensure maximum hamstring engagement.

fields.name: Glute-Ham Raise
fields.description: The Glute-Ham Raise is an exercise that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and lower back. Start by securing your feet and knees, then lower your torso forward from the knees while keeping your back straight, and return to the starting position. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and ensure proper muscle engagement.

fields.name: Single-Leg Romanian Deadlift
fields.description: The Single-Leg Romanian Deadlift targets the hamstrings, glutes, and core. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while lifting one leg behind you. Avoid rounding your back to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Kettlebell Swing
fields.description: The kettlebell swing is a dynamic exercise targeting the legs, glutes, and core. Start by hinging at the hips, not the knees, and use your hips to drive the kettlebell forward. Avoid using your arms to lift the kettlebell; let the momentum do the work.

fields.name: Cable Pull-Through
fields.description: The cable pull-through is a lower body exercise that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and lower back. Stand facing away from the cable machine, hinge at the hips, and pull the rope attachment through your legs while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to ensure proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Leg Press (Feet High)
fields.description: The Leg Press (Feet High) targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Position your feet higher on the platform to emphasize the glutes and hamstrings. Avoid locking your knees at the top of the movement to maintain tension and protect your joints.

fields.name: Standing Calf Raise (Machine)
fields.description: The Standing Calf Raise on a machine targets the calf muscles, primarily the gastrocnemius and soleus. Stand with your shoulders under the pads and the balls of your feet on the platform, then lift your heels to raise your body. Avoid bouncing at the top; control the movement for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Seated Calf Raise
fields.description: The seated calf raise targets the calf muscles, specifically the soleus. Sit with your feet on the platform and your knees at a 90-degree angle, then press through the balls of your feet to lift the weight. Avoid bouncing; focus on a controlled movement for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Donkey Calf Raise
fields.description: The Donkey Calf Raise targets the calf muscles, specifically the gastrocnemius and soleus. To perform it, lean forward with your hands on a stable surface and lift your heels off the ground by pushing through the balls of your feet. Avoid bouncing at the top; focus on a controlled movement.

fields.name: Single-Leg Calf Raise
fields.description: The single-leg calf raise targets the calf muscles, specifically the gastrocnemius and soleus. Stand on one leg with the ball of your foot on a raised surface, then lift your heel as high as possible. Avoid letting your ankle roll outward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Calf Raise on Leg Press
fields.description: The calf raise on leg press targets the calf muscles, specifically the gastrocnemius and soleus. To perform it, place the balls of your feet on the lower edge of the platform and extend your ankles to push the platform away. Avoid locking your knees to maintain proper form and reduce injury risk.

fields.name: Jump Rope (Calf Focus)
fields.description: Jump rope staying on balls of feet for calf endurance.

fields.name: Hip Thrust (Barbell)
fields.description: The Hip Thrust with a barbell is a powerful exercise targeting the glutes. Keep your upper back on a bench, feet flat on the ground, and drive through your heels to lift your hips until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Avoid arching your lower back by engaging your core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Hip Thrust (Dumbbell)
fields.description: The Hip Thrust with a dumbbell targets the glutes, helping to build strength and power. Keep your upper back against a bench, feet flat on the ground, and drive through your heels to lift your hips while holding the dumbbell on your lap. Avoid arching your lower back by engaging your core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Glute Bridge
fields.description: The glute bridge is an exercise that targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Lie on your back with knees bent, feet flat on the floor, and lift your hips until your body forms a straight line from shoulders to knees. Avoid arching your lower back by keeping your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Single-Leg Glute Bridge
fields.description: The single-leg glute bridge targets the glutes, hamstrings, and core. Lie on your back with one leg bent and the other extended, then lift your hips by pressing through the heel of the bent leg. Avoid letting your hips drop or twisting your torso; keep them level throughout the movement.

fields.name: Cable Kickbacks
fields.description: Cable kickbacks target the glutes and help build strength and definition in the lower body. Stand facing the cable machine, attach the ankle strap, and extend your leg straight back while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and maximize glute activation.

fields.name: Cable Pull-Throughs
fields.description: Cable Pull-Throughs target the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Stand facing away from the cable machine, hinge at the hips, and pull the rope attachment through your legs while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Sumo Squat
fields.description: The sumo squat is a lower body exercise that primarily targets the glutes, along with the inner thighs and quads. Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out, then lower your hips down and back as if sitting into a chair. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Step-Ups (Glute Focus)
fields.description: Step-ups with a glute focus target the glutes while also engaging the hamstrings and quads. Step onto a sturdy platform with your entire foot, driving through the heel to lift your body up. Avoid pushing off the back leg to ensure the glutes are doing the work.

fields.name: Lateral Band Walks
fields.description: Lateral Band Walks target the glutes and hip abductors. Keep the band just above your knees, maintain a slight squat, and step side-to-side without letting your knees cave in. Avoid dragging your feet to ensure full activation of the muscles.

fields.name: Clamshells
fields.description: Clamshells target the glutes, particularly the gluteus medius, and help improve hip stability. Lie on your side with knees bent and feet together, then lift your top knee while keeping your feet touching. Avoid rotating your hips or back to ensure the glutes are doing the work.

fields.name: Frog Pumps
fields.description: Frog Pumps are a glute-focused exercise that helps strengthen and tone the buttocks. Lie on your back with the soles of your feet together, knees bent, and thrust your hips upward while squeezing your glutes. Avoid arching your lower back to ensure the glutes do the work.

fields.name: Romanian Deadlift (Glute Focus)
fields.description: RDL with emphasis on squeezing glutes at top position.

fields.name: Plank
fields.description: The plank is an isometric core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, engaging your core and glutes. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise too high.

fields.name: Side Plank
fields.description: The side plank is a core exercise that targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and shoulders. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, with your elbow directly under your shoulder. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Dead Bug
fields.description: Lying on back, extend opposite arm and leg while maintaining back flat.

fields.name: Bird Dog
fields.description: The Bird Dog is a core exercise that also engages the lower back, glutes, and shoulders. Begin on all fours, extending one arm forward and the opposite leg back, keeping your hips level and core engaged. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a neutral spine throughout the movement.

fields.name: Hollow Body Hold
fields.description: The Hollow Body Hold is a core exercise that targets the abdominal muscles and helps improve overall core stability. Lie on your back, lift your shoulders and legs off the ground, and keep your lower back pressed into the floor. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and maximize core engagement.

fields.name: Bicycle Crunches
fields.description: Alternating elbow to opposite knee in cycling motion.

fields.name: Russian Twists
fields.description: Russian Twists are a core exercise that primarily targets the obliques and the rectus abdominis. Sit on the floor with your knees bent, lean back slightly, and rotate your torso side to side while keeping your core engaged. Avoid rounding your back to maintain proper form and prevent strain.

fields.name: Cable Woodchops
fields.description: Diagonal cable rotation for functional core strength.

fields.name: Hanging Leg Raises
fields.description: Hang from bar, raise legs to parallel or higher.

fields.name: Lying Leg Raises
fields.description: Lying leg raises target the core muscles, particularly the lower abs. Lie flat on your back with your legs straight, then lift them towards the ceiling while keeping your lower back pressed into the floor. Avoid arching your back to ensure maximum core engagement.

fields.name: Ab Wheel Rollout
fields.description: The Ab Wheel Rollout is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Start on your knees, grip the handles of the ab wheel, and roll forward while keeping your core tight and back straight. Avoid letting your hips sag to prevent strain on your lower back.

fields.name: Pallof Press
fields.description: The Pallof Press is an anti-rotation core exercise that targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and rectus abdominis. Stand perpendicular to a resistance band or cable, hold the handle at chest height, and press it straight out while resisting rotation. Avoid letting your shoulders or hips twist during the movement.

fields.name: Dragon Flags
fields.description: Dragon Flags are a challenging core exercise that primarily targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. To perform it, lie on a bench, grip the edge behind your head, and lift your body into a straight line from shoulders to feet, lowering slowly without arching your back. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper form and maximize core engagement.

fields.name: V-Ups
fields.description: V-Ups are a core exercise that targets the abdominal muscles and hip flexors. Lie on your back, extend your arms overhead, and simultaneously lift your legs and torso to form a V shape. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Mountain Climbers
fields.description: Mountain Climbers are a dynamic exercise that targets your core, shoulders, and legs. Start in a high plank position and quickly alternate bringing your knees towards your chest. Keep your hips low to avoid bouncing up and down.

fields.name: Treadmill Running
fields.description: Treadmill running is a cardio exercise that primarily targets the heart and lungs, while also engaging the legs and core. Maintain an upright posture with a slight forward lean and keep your strides consistent. Avoid holding onto the handrails to ensure a natural running form.

fields.name: Treadmill Walking (Incline)
fields.description: Treadmill Walking on an incline is a cardio exercise that targets your heart and lungs while engaging your leg muscles, especially the calves and hamstrings. Maintain a steady pace and keep your posture upright with your core engaged. Avoid holding onto the handrails too tightly, as this can reduce the workout's effectiveness.

fields.name: Stationary Bike
fields.description: The stationary bike is a cardio exercise that primarily targets the heart and lungs while also engaging the legs and glutes. Adjust the seat height so your knees have a slight bend at the bottom of each pedal stroke. Avoid leaning too heavily on the handlebars to maintain proper posture.

fields.name: Rowing Machine
fields.description: The rowing machine is a cardio exercise that engages your legs, core, and upper body. Keep your back straight and drive through your legs to initiate each stroke. Avoid hunching your shoulders to prevent strain.

fields.name: Stair Climber
fields.description: The stair climber is a cardio exercise that simulates climbing stairs, targeting your heart, lungs, and lower body muscles. Keep your back straight and use a steady pace to maintain control. Avoid leaning on the handrails to ensure maximum workout efficiency.

fields.name: Elliptical
fields.description: The elliptical is a cardio exercise that primarily targets the heart and lungs while engaging the legs and glutes. Maintain an upright posture with a slight bend in your knees and keep your core engaged. Avoid leaning on the handles to ensure a more effective workout.

fields.name: Jump Rope
fields.description: Jump rope is a cardio exercise that primarily targets the heart and lungs while also engaging the calves, quads, and core. Keep your elbows close to your body and use your wrists to turn the rope, jumping just high enough to clear it. Avoid jumping too high to reduce impact on your joints.

fields.name: Burpees
fields.description: Burpees are a full-body cardio exercise that primarily targets the legs, core, and upper body. Start in a standing position, drop into a squat, kick your feet back into a plank, return to squat, and jump up. Avoid letting your hips sag during the plank to protect your lower back.

fields.name: Box Jumps
fields.description: Box jumps are a dynamic cardio exercise that targets your legs, glutes, and core. Start by standing in front of a sturdy box or platform, bend your knees, swing your arms, and jump onto the box, landing softly with both feet. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you land to prevent injury.

fields.name: Battle Ropes
fields.description: Battle ropes are a dynamic cardio exercise that engages your arms, shoulders, and core. To perform it, stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the ropes firmly, and create waves by moving your arms up and down rapidly. Avoid letting your back arch; keep your core tight for stability.

fields.name: Assault Bike
fields.description: The assault bike is a high-intensity cardio exercise that engages both the upper and lower body, targeting the heart and lungs. Keep a steady rhythm by synchronizing your arm and leg movements while maintaining an upright posture. Avoid leaning too far forward to prevent unnecessary strain on your back.

fields.name: Swimming
fields.description: Swimming is a full-body cardio exercise that primarily targets the heart and lungs, while also engaging muscles in the arms, legs, and core. Focus on maintaining a streamlined body position and a steady breathing rhythm. Avoid lifting your head too high out of the water, as it can disrupt your form and efficiency.

fields.name: Barbell Clean
fields.description: The barbell clean is a full-body exercise that targets the legs, back, shoulders, and core. Begin by lifting the barbell from the floor to your shoulders in one fluid motion, keeping your back straight and using your legs to drive the movement. Avoid pulling with your arms; focus on generating power through your hips.

fields.name: Power Clean
fields.description: The power clean is a full-body exercise that targets the legs, back, shoulders, and arms. Begin by lifting the barbell from the floor to your shoulders in one explosive movement, keeping your back straight and core engaged. Avoid pulling with your arms too early; focus on driving through your legs and hips.

fields.name: Clean and Jerk
fields.description: The clean and jerk is a dynamic full-body exercise that targets the legs, back, shoulders, and arms. Start by lifting the barbell from the floor to your shoulders in one motion, then drive it overhead by extending your legs and arms. Avoid rounding your back during the lift to prevent injury.

fields.name: Snatch
fields.description: The snatch is a dynamic full-body exercise that primarily targets the shoulders, back, legs, and core. Begin by lifting the barbell from the ground to overhead in one fluid motion, keeping the bar close to your body. Avoid letting the bar drift away from your body to maintain control and balance.

fields.name: Thrusters
fields.description: Thrusters are a dynamic full-body exercise that targets the legs, core, and shoulders. Start by holding a barbell or dumbbells at shoulder height, perform a squat, and then drive through your heels to press the weights overhead as you stand up. Avoid letting your knees cave in during the squat to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Man Makers
fields.description: Man Makers are a full-body exercise that combines a push-up, row, squat, and overhead press, targeting muscles in the chest, back, shoulders, legs, and core. Start in a plank position with dumbbells, perform a push-up, row each dumbbell, jump to a squat, and press overhead. Avoid letting your hips sag during the plank and keep your core engaged throughout.

fields.name: Turkish Get-Up
fields.description: The Turkish Get-Up is a full-body exercise that targets the shoulders, core, hips, and legs. Begin by lying on your back with one arm extended holding a weight, then rise to a standing position while keeping the weight overhead. Avoid rushing the movement; focus on maintaining control and proper alignment throughout.

fields.name: Farmer's Walk
fields.description: The Farmer's Walk is a full-body exercise that targets the shoulders, core, forearms, and legs. To perform it, walk a set distance while holding heavy weights in each hand, keeping your back straight and shoulders down. Avoid letting the weights pull your shoulders forward.

fields.name: Sled Push
fields.description: The sled push is a full-body exercise that targets your legs, core, and upper body. Keep your back straight and drive through your legs as you push the sled forward. Avoid leaning too far forward, which can strain your lower back.

fields.name: Sled Pull
fields.description: The sled pull is a full-body exercise that targets the legs, core, and upper body. Keep your back straight and engage your core as you pull the sled towards you using a rope or handles. Avoid rounding your shoulders to maintain proper posture and prevent strain.

fields.name: Tire Flips
fields.description: Tire Flips are a dynamic full-body exercise that targets the legs, core, back, and shoulders. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, squat down, grip the bottom of the tire, and drive through your legs to lift and flip it forward. Avoid rounding your back to prevent injury.

fields.name: Wall Balls
fields.description: Wall Balls are a dynamic full-body exercise that targets the legs, core, and shoulders. Stand facing a wall, squat down, and explosively throw a medicine ball at a target on the wall, catching it as you descend back into a squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward during the squat to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Kettlebell Swings
fields.description: Kettlebell swings are a dynamic exercise that targets the full body, including the glutes, hamstrings, core, and shoulders. Start by hinging at the hips, keeping your back straight, and driving the kettlebell forward with your hips. Avoid using your arms to lift the kettlebell; focus on the power generated from your hips.

fields.name: Medicine Ball Slams
fields.description: Medicine Ball Slams are a dynamic exercise that targets the full body, engaging the core, shoulders, and legs. Start by lifting the medicine ball overhead with both hands, then slam it down to the ground with force, using your entire body. Avoid rounding your back; keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Bear Crawl
fields.description: The bear crawl is a full-body exercise that targets the shoulders, core, and legs. Start on all fours with knees slightly off the ground, then move forward by simultaneously stepping with your right hand and left foot, followed by your left hand and right foot. Keep your hips low to avoid arching your back.

fields.name: Test Custom Exercise
fields.description: A custom exercise for testing

fields.name: Overhead Press
fields.description: The overhead press is a strength exercise that targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a strong, stable core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Seated - DB
fields.description: The Seated Dumbbell Press targets the shoulder muscles, particularly the deltoids. Sit upright with your back supported, hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, and press them overhead until your arms are fully extended. Avoid arching your back by engaging your core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Arnold - DB
fields.description: The Seated Arnold Press with dumbbells targets the shoulder muscles, specifically the deltoids. Start with the weights in front of your shoulders, palms facing you, then rotate your palms outward as you press overhead. Avoid arching your back by keeping your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Scott - DB
fields.description: The Seated Scott Dumbbell Press targets the shoulder muscles, focusing on building strength and stability. Sit on a bench with back support, hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, and press upward until your arms are fully extended. Avoid arching your back by keeping your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Seated - BB - Close Grip
fields.description: The Seated Close Grip Barbell Press targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Keep your elbows close to your body as you press the barbell overhead to engage the shoulders effectively. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent unnecessary strain on the joints.

fields.name: Press - Seated - BB - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Seated Barbell Press with a Medium Grip targets the shoulders, specifically the deltoids, and also engages the triceps. Sit with your back straight, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maintain proper form.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Behind Neck - BB - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Seated Behind Neck Barbell Press targets the shoulders, specifically the deltoids, and also engages the triceps. Sit upright with a medium grip on the barbell, lowering it behind your head to just below ear level before pressing it back up. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maintain proper form.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Thick Bar - Close Grip
fields.description: The Seated Thick Bar Close Grip Press targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Keep your elbows close to your body as you press the bar overhead to engage the correct muscles. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent unnecessary shoulder strain.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Thick Bar - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Seated Thick Bar Press with a Medium Grip targets the shoulder muscles, focusing on the deltoids. Sit upright with your back supported, grip the thick bar at shoulder width, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Thick Multi-Angled Bar - Medium Grip - Neutral
fields.description: The Seated Thick Multi-Angled Bar Press with a Medium Neutral Grip targets the shoulder muscles, particularly the deltoids. Sit upright with your back supported, grip the bar with palms facing each other, and press it overhead while keeping your elbows slightly bent. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.description: The Seated Close Grip Pin Touch Press with a Barbell targets the shoulders, focusing on the top range of motion. Sit upright, grip the barbell with hands close together, and press upward until your arms are nearly fully extended. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent strain.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - BB - Close Grip - Mid Range
fields.description: The Seated Close Grip Pin Touch Barbell Press targets the shoulders, focusing on the mid-range of motion. Keep your grip close and press the barbell from the pins to just above your head, maintaining control. Avoid flaring your elbows out to prevent unnecessary shoulder strain.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Bar - Close Grip - Top Range
fields.description: The Seated Pin Touch Press with a Thick Bar and Close Grip targets the shoulders, focusing on the top range of motion. Sit upright with a close grip on the thick bar, pressing it from the pins to just above your head. Avoid letting your elbows flare out to maintain shoulder engagement and prevent strain.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Bar - Close Grip - Mid Range
fields.description: The Seated Pin Touch Press with a Thick Bar and Close Grip targets the shoulders, focusing on the deltoids. Sit upright with the bar at shoulder height, using a close grip, and press it up until your arms are almost fully extended. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Bar - Medium Grip - Top Range
fields.description: The Seated Pin Touch Press with a thick bar and medium grip targets the shoulders, focusing on the top range of motion. Sit upright, grip the bar with a medium width, and press upward until your arms are nearly straight, ensuring the bar touches the pins lightly. Avoid leaning back excessively to maintain shoulder engagement and prevent strain on the lower back.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Bar - Medium Grip - Mid Range
fields.description: The Seated Pin Touch Press with a Thick Bar and Medium Grip targets the shoulders, focusing on the deltoids. Sit upright, grip the bar at shoulder width, and press until your arms are parallel to the floor, ensuring the bar touches the pins. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Multi-Angled Bar - Medium Grip - Neutral - Top Range
fields.description: The Seated Pin Touch Press with a Thick Multi-Angled Bar using a Medium Grip targets the shoulder muscles, focusing on the top range of motion. Sit upright, grip the bar with a neutral hand position, and press upward until your arms are nearly straight, keeping tension on the shoulders. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Pin Touch - Thick Multi-Angled Bar - Medium Grip - Neutral - Mid Range
fields.description: The Seated Press with a Thick Multi-Angled Bar using a medium grip in a neutral position targets the shoulder muscles. Sit upright with your back supported, grip the bar with palms facing each other, and press upward until your arms are extended but not locked. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent strain.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - Arnold - DB
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Arnold Press with dumbbells targets the shoulder muscles, particularly the deltoids. Begin seated with your back unsupported, holding the dumbbells at shoulder height with palms facing you, then rotate your wrists as you press overhead. fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - Scott - DB
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Scott Dumbbell Press targets the shoulder muscles, focusing on the deltoids. Sit on a bench without back support, holding dumbbells at shoulder height with palms facing forward, and press them overhead. Avoid arching your back; keep your core engaged for stability.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - BB - Close Grip
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Close Grip Barbell Press targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Sit upright without back support, grip the barbell with hands closer than shoulder-width, and press it overhead. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - BB - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Barbell Press with a Medium Grip targets the shoulder muscles, primarily the deltoids, while also engaging the triceps and upper chest. Sit upright with your feet flat on the floor, grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, and press it overhead without leaning back. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - Behind Neck - BB - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Behind Neck Barbell Press targets the shoulders, focusing on the deltoids. Sit upright without back support, grip the barbell with a medium grip, and press it overhead, lowering it behind your head. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maintain proper form.

fields.name: Press - Seated - Unsupported - Thick Bar - Close Grip
fields.description: The Seated Unsupported Thick Bar Close Grip Press targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. fields.description: The Standing One-Arm Dumbbell Press targets the shoulder muscles, specifically the deltoids. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid leaning to the side; keep your torso upright throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Standing - DB
fields.description: The Standing Dumbbell Press targets the shoulder muscles, specifically the deltoids. Keep your core engaged and press the dumbbells overhead in a controlled motion. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a neutral spine throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Standing - Thick Multi-Angled Bar - Medium Grip - Neutral
fields.description: The Standing Press with a Thick Multi-Angled Bar using a Medium Grip and Neutral hand position targets the shoulder muscles, particularly the deltoids. Keep your core engaged and press the bar overhead in a controlled motion. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Standing - Javelin - BB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Standing Javelin Press with a Barbell targets the shoulders, focusing on unilateral strength and stability. Hold the barbell with one hand, keeping your core engaged, and press it overhead while maintaining a straight line from shoulder to wrist. Avoid leaning to one side; keep your body centered to prevent imbalance.

fields.name: Press - Standing - Javelin - Thick Bar - One-Arm
fields.description: The Standing Javelin Press with a Thick Bar targets the shoulders, engaging the core for stability. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the bar with one hand, and press it overhead while keeping your torso upright. Avoid leaning to one side; maintain a strong, stable core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Standing - Javelin - Cambered Bar - One-Arm
fields.description: The Standing Javelin Press with a Cambered Bar targets the shoulders, specifically the deltoids, while also engaging the core for stability. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the cambered bar with one hand, and press it overhead, keeping your core tight and back straight. Avoid leaning to one side or using momentum to lift the bar.

fields.name: Press - Z - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The One-Arm Z Press with a dumbbell targets the shoulders, core, and stabilizing muscles. Sit on the floor with legs extended, hold a dumbbell in one hand, and press it overhead while keeping your torso upright. Avoid leaning back or using momentum to lift the weight.

fields.name: Press - Z - DB
fields.description: The Press - Z - DB is a shoulder exercise that targets the deltoids, triceps, and upper chest. Sit on a bench with back support, hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, and press them overhead until your arms are fully extended. Avoid arching your back by engaging your core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Z - BB - Close Grip
fields.description: The Close Grip Z Press with a barbell targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Sit on the floor with legs extended, grip the barbell shoulder-width apart, and press it overhead while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a strong, upright posture throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Z - Thick Bar - Close Grip
fields.description: The Press - Z - Thick Bar - Close Grip targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest. Keep your elbows close to your body and press the bar overhead in a controlled motion. Avoid flaring your elbows out to maintain shoulder stability.

fields.name: Press - Z - Thick Bar - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Press - Z - Thick Bar - Medium Grip targets the shoulders, focusing on building strength and stability. Keep your core engaged and grip the thick bar with a medium width, pressing it overhead in a controlled motion. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Press - Z - Thick Multi-Angled Bar - Medium Grip - Neutral
fields.description: The Press with a Z-Thick Multi-Angled Bar using a medium grip and neutral wrist position targets the shoulder muscles. fields.name: Press - Sots - Heel Elevated - BB - Medium Grip
fields.description: The Heel Elevated Sots Press with a Barbell and Medium Grip targets the shoulders, core, and legs. Keep your heels elevated and maintain a stable squat position while pressing the barbell overhead. Avoid leaning forward; keep your chest up and core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Sots - BB
fields.description: The Sots Press with a barbell targets the shoulders, core, and upper back while also engaging the legs. Start in a deep squat position with the barbell resting on your shoulders, then press the bar overhead while maintaining the squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward; keep them aligned with your toes.

fields.name: Press - Half-Kneeling - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The half-kneeling one-arm dumbbell press targets the shoulder muscles while also engaging the core for stability. Start in a half-kneeling position with one knee on the ground and the opposite foot flat, pressing the dumbbell overhead with the same-side arm. Avoid arching your back; keep your core tight and spine neutral throughout the movement.

fields.name: Press - Half-Kneeling - Low Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Half-Kneeling Low Pulley One-Arm Press targets the shoulders, engaging the core for stability. Start in a half-kneeling position with the cable in one hand, pressing forward while keeping your torso upright. Avoid leaning or twisting your body as you press.

fields.name: Push Press - BB - Medium Grip - Front Rack
fields.description: The Push Press with a barbell in a medium grip front rack position primarily targets the shoulders, while also engaging the triceps and upper chest. Begin by holding the barbell at shoulder height, feet shoulder-width apart, and use a slight dip in your knees to drive the bar overhead. Avoid leaning back excessively to prevent lower back strain.

fields.name: Push Press - BB - Medium Grip - Behind the Neck
fields.description: The Push Press with a barbell using a medium grip behind the neck targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper back. Start with the barbell resting on your upper traps, then dip slightly at the knees and drive the bar overhead using your legs and shoulders. Avoid arching your lower back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Incline Press
fields.description: The incline press is an exercise targeting the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your back flat against the bench and press the weights up in a controlled motion. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Press - Incline - DB - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Incline Dumbbell Press on a Swiss Ball targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your core engaged and your feet firmly planted on the ground as you press the dumbbells upward. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a stable position on the ball.

fields.name: Press - Incline - DB - Swiss Ball - One-Arm
fields.description: The Incline Dumbbell Press on a Swiss Ball with One Arm targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps while engaging the core for stability. Keep your feet firmly planted and your core tight as you press the dumbbell upward, maintaining control throughout the movement. Avoid letting your hips sag; keep them elevated to ensure proper form and balance.

fields.name: Press - 65 Incline - DB
fields.description: The 65 Incline Dumbbell Press targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your back flat against the bench and press the dumbbells upward in a controlled motion. Avoid flaring your elbows too wide to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.description: The 55 Incline Dumbbell Press targets the upper chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your back firmly against the bench and press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended. Avoid letting your elbows flare out too much to prevent shoulder strain.

fields.name: Press - 55 Incline - BB - Close Grip
