Keep your chest pressed against the bench and raise the dumbbell to shoulder height with a controlled motion. Avoid swinging the weight; focus on using your back muscles to lift.

fields.name: Powell Raise - 35 Incline - DB
fields.description: The Powell Raise on a 35 incline with dumbbells targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Keep your chest against the bench and lift the dumbbell with a controlled motion, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blades together. Avoid using momentum to lift the weight; control is key for effectiveness.

fields.name: Powell Raise - 15 Incline - DB
fields.description: The Powell Raise on a 15 incline with dumbbells targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Keep your chest against the bench and lift the dumbbell to shoulder height with a controlled motion. Avoid swinging the weight; focus on using your back muscles to lift.

fields.name: Powell Raise - Flat - DB
fields.description: The Powell Raise - Flat - DB targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Lie on your side on a flat bench, holding a dumbbell in the top hand, and raise it perpendicular to your body while keeping your arm straight. Avoid swinging the weight; focus on controlled movements to engage the back muscles effectively.

fields.name: Powell Raise - Floor - DB
fields.description: The Powell Raise on the floor with dumbbells targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Lie on your side with a dumbbell in the top hand, keeping your arm straight as you lift it towards the ceiling. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Powell Raise - Swiss Ball - DB
fields.description: The Powell Raise on a Swiss Ball with dumbbells targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Lie face down on the Swiss ball with feet anchored, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and raise your arm to the side while keeping your elbow slightly bent. Avoid swinging the weight; control the movement to engage the back muscles effectively.

fields.name: Powell Raise - High Pulley
fields.description: The Powell Raise - High Pulley targets the upper back, specifically the rear deltoids and rhomboids. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, grasp the pulley handle with one hand, and pull it across your body while keeping your arm slightly bent. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements to engage the back muscles effectively.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 45 Incline - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone 45 Incline Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on a 45-degree incline bench, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and lift your arm up and out at a 45-degree angle. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to ensure proper isolation of the target muscles.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 45 Incline - DB
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone 45 Incline Dumbbell exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on an incline bench set at 45 degrees, holding dumbbells with arms extended and palms facing each other, then lift them to shoulder height. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to keep the focus on the lower traps.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 35 Incline - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone 35 Incline Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on an incline bench set at 35 degrees, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and lift it diagonally overhead while keeping your arm straight. Avoid shrugging your shoulder to ensure the focus remains on the lower traps.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 35 Incline - DB
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone 35 Incline Dumbbell exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on an incline bench set at 35 degrees, holding a dumbbell in each hand with arms extended downward, then raise them to form a Y shape. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to ensure proper muscle engagement.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 15 Incline - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone 15 Incline Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on a 15-degree incline bench, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and lift your arm straight up, keeping your elbow slightly bent. Avoid shrugging your shoulder to ensure proper engagement of the lower traps.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - 15 Incline - DB
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone on a 15 Incline with Dumbbells targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on an incline bench, holding dumbbells with arms hanging straight down, then lift them outward to form a Y shape. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to ensure proper muscle engagement.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - Flat - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone Flat Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on a flat bench, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and lift it straight up with your arm extended. Avoid rotating your torso; keep your body stable throughout the movement.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - Flat - DB
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone Flat DB exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on a flat bench, holding dumbbells with arms extended downward, then raise them to form a Y shape with your body. Avoid shrugging your shoulders to keep the focus on the lower traps.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Prone - Floor - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Prone Floor Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Lie face down on the floor, holding a dumbbell in one hand, and lift your arm straight up, keeping your thumb pointing up. Avoid arching your back; focus on controlled movement.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Bent-Over - Supported - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Bent-Over Supported Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Keep your back flat and hinge at the hips while supporting yourself with one arm on a bench. Avoid rounding your back to maintain proper form and prevent strain.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Bent-Over - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Bent-Over Dumbbell One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and rear deltoids. Keep your back flat and hinge at the hips, lifting the dumbbell in a controlled motion. Avoid using momentum; focus on isolating the shoulder muscles.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Facing - Mid Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Facing Mid Pulley One-Arm exercise targets the shoulders, specifically the lower trapezius. Stand facing a mid pulley machine with one arm extended, pulling the handle towards your torso while keeping your elbow slightly bent. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements to engage the correct muscles.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Facing - Low Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Facing Low Pulley One-Arm exercise targets the lower trapezius and shoulder muscles. Stand facing a low pulley with a handle in one hand, pull the handle diagonally upward while keeping your arm straight. Avoid rotating your torso; focus on controlled movement.

fields.name: Trap 3 - Sideway - Low Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Trap 3 Sideway Low Pulley One-Arm exercise targets the shoulders, specifically the trapezius and deltoids. Stand sideways to the low pulley with feet shoulder-width apart, grasp the handle with one hand, and pull it across your body while keeping your arm straight. Avoid rotating your torso; focus on isolating the shoulder movement.

fields.name: Neck Extension - Standing - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Neck Extension - Standing - Swiss Ball targets the neck muscles, improving strength and flexibility. Stand with your back against a wall, place the Swiss ball behind your head, and gently press your head into the ball while keeping your spine aligned. Avoid tilting your head too far back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Neck Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Neck Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball targets the neck extensors and stabilizes the upper spine. Lie on your back with your head resting on a Swiss ball, gently extending your neck backward while keeping your shoulders relaxed. Avoid overextending your neck to prevent strain.

fields.name: Neck Extension - Head Harness - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Neck Extension with a Head Harness on a Low Pulley targets the neck extensors, helping to strengthen and stabilize the neck. Keep your back straight and slowly extend your neck backward, ensuring controlled movement. Avoid jerking your head to prevent strain or injury.

fields.name: Pinch Block - Small - One-Arm
fields.description: The Pinch Block - Small - One-Arm exercise targets the forearms and grip strength. Hold a small pinch block with one hand, keeping your wrist straight and your shoulder relaxed. Avoid using your thumb to grip the block too tightly, as it reduces the effectiveness of the exercise.

fields.name: Pinch Block - Medium - One-Arm
fields.description: The Pinch Block - Medium - One-Arm exercise targets the forearms and grip strength. Hold a medium-sized pinch block with one hand, keeping your arm straight and your shoulder relaxed. Avoid leaning your body to compensate for grip fatigue.

fields.name: Pinch Block - Large - One-Arm
fields.description: KILO category: Forearms - Grip

fields.name: Pinch Card - One-Arm
fields.description: KILO category: Forearms - Grip

fields.name: Radial Flexion - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm
fields.description: KILO category: Forearms - Wrist

fields.name: Ulnar Flexion - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm
fields.description: The Ulnar Flexion - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm exercise targets the forearm muscles, specifically focusing on the ulnar side. Hold a hammer or similar weight with one hand, arm extended in front of you, and flex your wrist inward towards your body. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to assist in the movement; keep the motion isolated to the wrist.

fields.name: Wrist Supination - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Supination - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm targets the forearm muscles, specifically the supinators. Hold a hammer or similar object in one hand with your arm bent at 90 degrees, then rotate your wrist to turn the hammer from a vertical to a horizontal position. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to assist in the movement; focus on isolating the wrist.

fields.name: Wrist Supination - Mid Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Supination - Mid Pulley - One-Arm exercise targets the forearm muscles, specifically the supinator. Stand facing a mid pulley machine, grasp the handle with one hand, and rotate your wrist outward while keeping your elbow close to your side. Avoid using your shoulder to initiate the movement; focus on isolating the wrist.

fields.name: Wrist Pronation - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Pronation - Thor's Hammer - One-Arm exercise targets the forearm muscles, specifically focusing on the pronators. Hold a hammer or a similar weighted object vertically in one hand, and rotate your wrist inward to bring the hammer head down, then return to the starting position. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to assist in the movement; keep the motion isolated to the wrist.

fields.name: Wrist Pronation - Mid Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Pronation - Mid Pulley - One-Arm exercise targets the forearm muscles, specifically focusing on pronation strength. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grip the handle with one hand, and rotate your wrist inward against the resistance. Avoid using your shoulder or upper arm to assist in the movement; keep the motion isolated to the wrist.

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - DB
fields.description: Wrist Flexion with Dumbbells targets the forearm muscles, specifically the wrist flexors. Sit with your forearm resting on your thigh, palm facing up, and curl the dumbbell towards your forearm by bending at the wrist. Avoid using your entire arm to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Flexion with Dumbbell - One-Arm targets the forearm muscles, specifically the wrist flexors. Sit on a bench with your forearm resting on your thigh, palm facing up, and curl the dumbbell towards your body using only your wrist. Avoid moving your elbow or shoulder to ensure the focus remains on the wrist flexors.

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Wrist Flexion - Low Pulley exercise targets the forearm flexor muscles. Sit on a bench with your forearm resting on your thigh, palm facing up, and use a low pulley to curl your wrist upward. Avoid using your entire arm; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - Low Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: KILO category: Forearms - Forearm Flexors

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - BB
fields.description: Wrist Flexion with a barbell targets the forearm flexor muscles. Sit on a bench, rest your forearms on your thighs, and hold the barbell with an underhand grip, allowing your wrists to hang over your knees. Avoid using your shoulders or upper arms to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Flexion - EZ Bar
fields.description: The Wrist Flexion with an EZ Bar targets the forearm flexor muscles. Sit on a bench, rest your forearms on your thighs, and hold the EZ bar with an underhand grip, then curl your wrists upward. Avoid using your entire arm to lift the bar; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Extension - DB
fields.description: The Wrist Extension with Dumbbells targets the forearm extensor muscles. Sit with your forearm resting on your thigh, palm facing down, and slowly lift the dumbbell by extending your wrist. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Extension - DB - One-Arm
fields.description: KILO category: Forearms - Forearm Extensors

fields.name: Wrist Extension - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Wrist Extension - Low Pulley targets the forearm extensor muscles. Stand facing a low pulley machine, grip the handle with an underhand grip, and extend your wrist upward while keeping your forearm stable. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Extension - Low Pulley - One-Arm
fields.description: The Wrist Extension - Low Pulley - One-Arm exercise targets the forearm extensor muscles. Stand facing the low pulley, grip the handle with one hand, and extend your wrist upward while keeping your forearm steady. Avoid using your shoulder or elbow to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Extension - BB
fields.description: The Wrist Extension with a barbell targets the forearm extensor muscles. Sit on a bench, rest your forearms on your thighs, and hold the barbell with an overhand grip, then lift your hands upward by extending your wrists. Avoid using your shoulders or elbows to lift the weight; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Extension - EZ Bar
fields.description: The Wrist Extension with an EZ Bar targets the forearm extensor muscles. Sit on a bench, rest your forearms on your thighs with your wrists hanging over the edge, and grip the EZ bar with palms facing down. Avoid using your shoulders or upper arms to lift the bar; focus on isolating the wrist movement.

fields.name: Wrist Roller
fields.description: The wrist roller is an arm exercise that primarily targets the forearms and grip strength. Hold the roller with both hands and use your wrists to wind the weight up and down the rope. Avoid using your shoulders or upper arms to ensure the forearms do the work.

fields.name: Squat
fields.description: The squat is a fundamental exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips back and down as if sitting in a chair, keeping your chest up and knees over your toes. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Safety Bar Squat is a leg exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you descend, ensuring your knees track over your toes. Avoid letting your lower back round at the bottom of the squat.

fields.name: Squat - Cambered Bar
fields.description: The Squat with a Cambered Bar targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower your hips back and down, ensuring your knees track over your toes. Avoid letting your lower back round by maintaining a neutral spine throughout the movement.

fields.name: Front Squat
fields.description: The front squat is a compound exercise targeting the quadriceps, glutes, and core. Keep your elbows high and chest up as you lower into the squat to maintain balance and form. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to prevent strain and injury.

fields.name: Squat - Goblet - DB
fields.description: The Goblet Squat with a dumbbell targets the quads, hamstrings, glutes, and core. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both hands, keep your chest up, and lower your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Goblet - Heels Elevated - DB
fields.description: The Goblet Squat with heels elevated targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, glutes, and hamstrings. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest and squat down, keeping your heels elevated to increase range of motion. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you lower into the squat.

fields.name: Squat - Goblet - Quad - DB
fields.description: The Goblet Squat with a dumbbell primarily targets the quadriceps, while also engaging the glutes and hamstrings. Hold the dumbbell close to your chest, keep your chest up, and push your hips back as you lower into the squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Goblet - Cyclist - DB
fields.description: The Goblet Cyclist Squat with dumbbells targets the quads, glutes, and hamstrings. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest, keep your feet close together, and squat down while maintaining an upright torso. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat.

fields.name: Squat - Hack
fields.description: The hack squat is a leg exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your back flat against the pad and push through your heels as you lower and raise the weight. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Hack - DB
fields.description: The Dumbbell Hack Squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding dumbbells behind your legs, and lower into a squat while keeping your chest up and back straight. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat down.

fields.name: Squat - Hack - BB
fields.description: The Hack Squat with a barbell targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with your back against a wall, feet shoulder-width apart, and hold the barbell behind your legs as you squat down. Avoid letting your knees extend past your toes to protect your joints.

fields.name: Squat - Cyclist - DB
fields.description: The Cyclist Dumbbell Squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with your heels elevated on a small platform, holding dumbbells at your sides, and squat down while keeping your chest up and core engaged. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you lower into the squat.

fields.name: Squat - Cyclist - BB
fields.description: The Cyclist Barbell Squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, emphasizing the quads. Stand with your heels elevated on a small platform or weight plate, holding the barbell across your upper back, and squat down while keeping your chest up and core engaged. Avoid letting your knees cave inwards as you lower into the squat.

fields.name: Squat - Cyclist - Trap Bar
fields.description: The Cyclist Squat with a Trap Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with your feet close together and heels elevated, gripping the trap bar handles, then lower into a squat while keeping your chest up and back straight. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you push through your heels to stand back up.

fields.name: Squat - Cyclist - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Cyclist Squat with a Safety Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your feet close together and elevated on a wedge or small platform to emphasize the quads, while maintaining an upright torso. Avoid letting your knees cave inward; focus on pushing them outward as you squat.

fields.name: Squat - Cyclist - Cambered Bar
fields.description: The Cyclist Squat with a Cambered Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your heels elevated and maintain an upright torso as you lower into the squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to ensure proper alignment and reduce injury risk.

fields.name: Squat - Quad - DB
fields.description: The Dumbbell Squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at your sides, keep your chest up, and lower your hips back and down as if sitting in a chair. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat.

fields.name: Squat - Quad - BB
fields.description: The Barbell Squat primarily targets the quadriceps, while also engaging the hamstrings, glutes, and core. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, barbell resting on your upper back, and lower your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment and prevent injury.

fields.name: Squat - Quad - Trap Bar
fields.description: The Squat with a Trap Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand inside the trap bar, grip the handles, and keep your chest up as you lower into a squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Quad - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Squat with a Safety Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower your hips back and down. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Quad - Cambered Bar
fields.description: The Squat with a Cambered Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower your hips back and down, ensuring your knees track over your toes. fields.name: Squat - Heels Elevated - DB
fields.description: The heels elevated dumbbell squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged while holding a dumbbell in each hand, and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you lower your body.

fields.name: Squat - Heels Elevated - BB
fields.description: The Squat - Heels Elevated - BB targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with your heels elevated on a small platform, holding a barbell across your upper back, and lower into a squat while keeping your chest up. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat down.

fields.name: Squat - Heels Elevated - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Squat - Heels Elevated - Safety Bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower into the squat, ensuring your knees track over your toes. Avoid letting your heels lift off the platform to maintain stability and proper form.

fields.name: Squat - Heels Elevated - Cambered Bar

fields.name: Squat - Hatfield - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Hatfield Squat with a safety bar targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your chest up and engage your core as you descend, using the handles for balance and support. Avoid leaning too far forward to maintain proper form and prevent strain on your lower back.

fields.name: Squat - To Box - Bottom Range - BB
fields.description: The Squat to Box - Bottom Range with a Barbell targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Lower yourself slowly to the box, keeping your chest up and core engaged, then drive through your heels to stand back up. Avoid bouncing off the box to maintain control and prevent injury.

fields.name: Squat - Wide Stance - BB
fields.description: The Wide Stance Barbell Squat targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and inner thighs. Stand with feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out, and keep your chest up as you lower into the squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Wide Stance - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Squat - Wide Stance - Safety Bar targets the legs, focusing on the quads, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and maintain a strong core as you lower into the squat. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to ensure proper alignment and reduce injury risk.

fields.name: Squat - Wide Stance - Cambered Bar
fields.description: KILO category: Squat - Long Range

fields.name: Squat - Zercher - BB
fields.description: The Zercher Squat with a barbell targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and core. Hold the barbell in the crook of your elbows, keep your chest up, and squat down while maintaining a straight back. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you rise.

fields.name: Squat - Zercher - Thick Bar
fields.description: The Zercher Squat with a thick bar targets the legs, focusing on the quads, hamstrings, and glutes, while also engaging the core and upper back. Hold the bar in the crook of your elbows, keep your chest up, and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the ground. fields.name: Squat - Zercher - Heels Elevated - BB
fields.description: The Zercher Squat with heels elevated primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Hold the barbell in the crook of your elbows and keep your chest up as you squat down, ensuring your knees track over your toes. fields.name: Squat - Zercher - Quad - Thick Bar
fields.description: The Zercher squat with a thick bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, while also engaging the core. Hold the bar in the crook of your elbows, keep your chest up, and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the ground. fields.name: Squat - Zercher - Cyclist - BB

fields.name: Squat - Zercher - Cyclist - Thick Bar
fields.description: The Zercher Cyclist Squat with a thick bar targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your heels elevated and maintain an upright torso as you hold the bar in the crook of your elbows. Avoid letting your knees cave in as you squat down.

fields.name: Squat - Zombie - Heels Elevated - BB
fields.description: The Zombie Squat with heels elevated using a barbell targets the quads, glutes, and hamstrings. Keep your arms extended in front of you like a zombie to maintain balance and ensure your heels are slightly elevated to increase quad activation. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat down.

fields.name: Squat - Zombie - BB
fields.description: The Zombie Barbell Squat is a leg exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Hold the barbell across the front of your shoulders with arms extended forward like a zombie, keeping your chest up and core engaged as you squat down. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Front Squat - Heels Elevated - BB
fields.description: The Front Squat with Heels Elevated using a Barbell targets the quadriceps, glutes, and core. Keep your chest up and elbows high as you descend, ensuring your knees track over your toes. Avoid letting your heels lift off the platform to maintain balance and proper form.

fields.name: Front Squat - Quad - BB
fields.description: The front squat with a barbell targets the quadriceps, glutes, and core. Keep your elbows high and chest up to maintain balance and proper form. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat down.

fields.name: Front Squat - Cyclist - BB
fields.description: The Front Squat - Cyclist with a barbell targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Keep your heels elevated on a small platform or weight plate to emphasize quad activation and maintain an upright torso. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you squat down.

fields.name: Squat - Overhead - Hack - BB
fields.description: The Overhead Hack Squat with a barbell targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the barbell overhead, and lower into a squat while keeping your chest up and core engaged. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Overhead - Cyclist - BB
fields.description: The Overhead Cyclist Squat with a barbell targets the legs, particularly the quadriceps, while also engaging the core and shoulders. Keep your feet elevated on small plates and press the barbell overhead, maintaining a tight core as you squat down. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to ensure proper alignment and prevent injury.

fields.name: Squat - Overhead - Quad - BB
fields.description: The Overhead Barbell Squat targets the quads, hamstrings, glutes, and core. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold the barbell overhead with arms fully extended, and lower into a squat while keeping the chest up and core engaged. Avoid letting the knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Overhead - Heels Elevated - BB
fields.description: The Overhead Squat with Heels Elevated using a Barbell targets the legs, core, and shoulders. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you press the bar overhead and squat down, ensuring your heels stay elevated on a platform. Avoid letting your knees cave inward as you lower into the squat.

fields.name: Squat - Overhead - BB
fields.description: The Overhead Barbell Squat targets the legs, core, and shoulders, enhancing strength and stability. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you lower into a squat, ensuring the barbell stays directly overhead. Avoid letting your knees cave inward to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Sissy
fields.description: The Sissy Squat is a leg exercise that primarily targets the quadriceps while also engaging the core. Keep your body straight from knees to head and lean back as you bend your knees forward, lowering your body. Avoid letting your hips drop or sticking your butt out to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Squat - Telemark - BB
fields.description: The Squat - Telemark - BB is a leg exercise targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back, and lower into a squat while stepping one foot back into a lunge position. Avoid letting your front knee extend past your toes to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Squat - Telemark - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Squat - Telemark - Safety Bar targets the legs, focusing on the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. fields.name: Nordic Curl - Inertia
fields.description: The Nordic Curl - Inertia targets the hamstrings, glutes, and calves by controlling your body as you lower it from a kneeling position. Keep your body straight from head to knees and lower yourself slowly, using your hamstrings to resist the fall. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Nordic Curl - Accentuated Eccentric - DB
fields.description: The Nordic Curl with Accentuated Eccentric using a dumbbell targets the hamstrings and glutes. Focus on controlling the descent slowly while keeping your body straight from knees to shoulders. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper form and maximize muscle engagement.

fields.name: Glute Bridge - Unilateral
fields.description: The unilateral glute bridge targets the glutes and also engages the hamstrings and core. Lie on your back with one knee bent and the other leg extended, then lift your hips by pressing through the heel of the bent leg. Avoid letting your hips drop or rotate; keep them level throughout the movement.

fields.name: Hip Extension - Supine
fields.description: The Hip Extension - Supine targets the glutes by lifting your hips while lying on your back. Keep your core engaged and press through your heels as you raise your hips towards the ceiling. Avoid arching your lower back to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Hip Extension - Supine - Unilateral
fields.description: The Hip Extension - Supine - Unilateral targets the glutes by lifting one leg while lying on your back. Keep your core engaged and press through your heel to lift your hips off the ground. Avoid arching your lower back to ensure the glutes do the work.

fields.name: Hip Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Hip Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball targets the glutes by lifting your hips while lying on your back with your feet on a Swiss ball. Keep your core engaged and press through your heels to lift your hips until your body forms a straight line from shoulders to knees. Avoid letting the ball roll away by maintaining control throughout the movement.

fields.name: Hip Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball - Unilateral
fields.description: The Hip Extension - Supine - Swiss Ball - Unilateral targets the glutes by lifting one leg while lying on your back with your feet on a Swiss ball. Keep your core engaged and press through the heel of the working leg to lift your hips. Avoid letting your hips sag or rotating your pelvis during the movement.

fields.name: King Deadlift - Mid Range

fields.name: King Deadlift
fields.description: The King Deadlift is a single-leg deadlift variation that primarily targets the glutes. Focus on keeping your back straight and hinging at the hips as you lift one leg behind you. Avoid twisting your torso to maintain balance and proper form.

fields.name: King Deadlift - DB
fields.description: The King Deadlift with dumbbells targets the glutes while also engaging the hamstrings and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips as you lower the dumbbells towards the floor. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - Low Pulley - Wide Stance
fields.description: The Seated Goodmorning on a Low Pulley with a Wide Stance targets the glutes and lower back. Sit with feet wide apart, hold the pulley handle, and hinge forward at the hips while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to ensure proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - Low Pulley - Medium Stance

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - DB - Wide Stance

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - BB - Wide Stance

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - BB - Medium Stance
fields.description: The seated barbell good morning targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Sit on a bench with feet shoulder-width apart, holding the barbell across your upper back, and hinge forward at the hips while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - Cambered Bar - Wide Stance
fields.description: The Seated Goodmorning with a Cambered Bar and Wide Stance targets the glutes, lower back, and hamstrings. Sit upright on a bench with feet wide, hinge at the hips to lower your torso forward while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and maintain proper form.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Seated - Cambered Bar - Medium Stance
fields.description: The Seated Goodmorning with a Cambered Bar targets the glutes, lower back, and hamstrings. Sit on a bench with feet shoulder-width apart, keep your back straight, and hinge at the hips to lower your torso forward. fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - B Stance - BB
fields.description: The B Stance Barbell Goodmorning is a glute-focused exercise that also engages the hamstrings and lower back. Stand with one foot slightly behind the other, holding a barbell across your upper back, and hinge at the hips while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and maximize glute activation.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - B Stance - Safety Bar

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - B Stance - Cambered Bar

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - BB - Wide Stance
fields.description: The Goodmorning with a barbell in a wide stance targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips, lowering your torso until it's nearly parallel to the ground. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - BB - Medium Stance
fields.description: The Goodmorning with a barbell in a medium stance primarily targets the glutes, along with the hamstrings and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips, lowering your torso until it's almost parallel to the ground. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - Safety Bar
fields.description: The Goodmorning with a safety bar is a strength exercise targeting the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Keep your core engaged and hinge at the hips while maintaining a slight bend in the knees. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - Cambered Bar
fields.description: The Standing Goodmorning with a Cambered Bar targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while maintaining a slight bend in the knees. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and ensure proper form.

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - Pin Touch - Safety Bar - Mid Range

fields.name: Goodmorning - Standing - Pin Touch - Safety Bar - Bottom Range

fields.name: Jefferson Curl - BB
fields.description: The Jefferson Curl with a barbell is a flexibility and strength exercise targeting the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. fields.name: Back Extension - Incline
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline targets the glutes, lower back, and hamstrings. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips as you lift your torso. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Incline - DB
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline - DB targets the glutes and lower back. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest, hinge at the hips, and lift your upper body until it's in line with your legs. Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Incline - DB - Accentuated Eccentric
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline - DB - Accentuated Eccentric targets the glutes by extending the hips while controlling the descent. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest, extend your hips at the top, and slowly lower your body back to the starting position. Avoid arching your lower back to maintain proper form and focus on the glutes.

fields.name: Back Extension - Incline - Front - BB
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline - Front - BB targets the glutes and lower back. Lie face down on an incline bench with a barbell held at the back of your neck, then extend your torso upward by engaging your glutes. Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Incline - Back - BB
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline - Back - BB targets the glutes and lower back. Lie face down on an incline bench, holding a barbell across your upper back, and extend your torso upwards by squeezing your glutes. Avoid arching your lower back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Incline - Bands
fields.description: The Back Extension - Incline - Bands targets the glutes by using resistance bands while performing the exercise on an incline. Keep your core engaged and squeeze your glutes as you lift your torso. Avoid arching your lower back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Deadlift - Single-Leg Romanian - Low Pulley - Rope
fields.description: The Single-Leg Romanian Deadlift with a low pulley and rope targets the glutes, hamstrings, and core. fields.name: Deadlift - Single-Leg Romanian - DB

fields.name: Deadlift - Single-Leg Romanian - BB - Contralateral

fields.name: Deadlift - Romanian - DB
fields.description: The Romanian Dumbbell Deadlift targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips while lowering the dumbbells along your legs. Avoid rounding your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Deadlift - Romanian - BB - Medium Grip

fields.name: Deadlift - Romanian - BB - Wide Grip

fields.name: Pull-Through - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Pull-Through on a low pulley targets the glutes and hamstrings. Stand facing away from the machine, grab the rope handle between your legs, and hinge at the hips while keeping your back straight. Avoid rounding your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Hip Thrust - Machine
fields.description: The Hip Thrust on a machine targets the glutes, helping to build strength and power in your lower body. Position your upper back against the pad, feet flat on the platform, and drive through your heels to lift your hips. Avoid arching your lower back; keep your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Hip Thrust - Machine - Unilateral
fields.description: The Hip Thrust - Machine - Unilateral targets the glutes by isolating each side individually for balanced strength development. Ensure your back is firmly against the pad and drive through your heel to lift your hips. Avoid arching your lower back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Hip Thrust - Machine - Banded
fields.description: The Hip Thrust on a machine with a band targets the glutes, enhancing strength and muscle activation. Keep your feet flat and drive through your heels, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. Avoid arching your lower back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal
fields.description: The Back Extension - Horizontal targets the glutes and lower back muscles. Keep your core engaged and lift your upper body until it's in line with your legs. Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal - DB
fields.description: The Back Extension - Horizontal - DB targets the glutes while also engaging the lower back and hamstrings. Hold a dumbbell close to your chest, hinge at the hips, and lift your torso until it's in line with your legs. Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal - DB - Accentuated Eccentric

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal - Front - BB

Avoid arching your back excessively to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal - Back - BB
fields.description: The Back Extension - Horizontal - Back - BB targets the glutes and lower back. Keep your back straight and hinge at the hips to lift your torso while holding a barbell across your shoulders. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain.

fields.name: Back Extension - Horizontal - Unilateral
fields.description: The Back Extension - Horizontal - Unilateral targets the glutes and lower back by isolating one side at a time. Keep your core engaged and lift one leg while maintaining a neutral spine. Avoid rotating your hips to ensure proper glute activation.

fields.name: Reverse Hyper
fields.description: The Reverse Hyper targets the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. Lie face down on a bench with your hips at the edge, then lift your legs behind you until they are in line with your torso. Avoid swinging your legs too quickly to maintain control and maximize muscle engagement.

fields.name: Reverse Hyper - Unilateral
fields.description: The Reverse Hyper - Unilateral targets the glutes by lifting one leg at a time while lying face down on a bench. Keep your core engaged and lift your leg until it's in line with your body, avoiding any excessive arching of the lower back. Avoid swinging your leg for momentum to ensure controlled movement.

fields.name: Calf Raise - Squat - Toes Elevated
fields.description: The Calf Raise - Squat - Toes Elevated targets the calves, quadriceps, and glutes. Stand with your toes elevated on a small platform, perform a squat, then rise up onto your toes for a calf raise. Avoid letting your knees cave inward during the squat to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Calf Raise - Seated - Machine
fields.description: The seated calf raise machine targets the calf muscles, specifically the soleus. Sit with your feet on the platform and your knees under the pads, then push through the balls of your feet to raise your heels. Avoid bouncing the weight; focus on controlled movements for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Calf Raise - Seated - Machine - Unilateral
fields.description: The seated unilateral calf raise machine targets the calf muscles, specifically the gastrocnemius and soleus. Sit with one foot on the platform and the pad resting on your thigh, then push through the ball of your foot to raise your heel. Avoid bouncing or using momentum to ensure maximum muscle engagement.

fields.name: Anterior Tibialis Raise - Standing
fields.description: The Anterior Tibialis Raise - Standing targets the muscles along the front of your lower legs, specifically the anterior tibialis. fields.name: Anterior Tibialis Raise - Seated - Banded - Unilateral

fields.name: Anterior Tibialis Raise - Machine - Seated

fields.name: Plank - Front
fields.description: The front plank is an isometric exercise targeting the core muscles, including the abdominals and lower back. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, with elbows directly under your shoulders. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise; maintain a neutral spine.

fields.name: Plank - Front - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Plank - Front - Swiss Ball is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Position your forearms on the Swiss ball and keep your body in a straight line from head to heels. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Plank - Side
fields.description: The side plank targets the obliques and other core muscles. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, supporting yourself on one forearm and the side of your foot. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Plank - Birddog
fields.description: The Plank - Birddog is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, lower back, and stabilizing muscles. Start in a plank position, then extend one arm forward and the opposite leg back, keeping your body stable. Avoid letting your hips sag or rotate; maintain a straight line from head to heel.

fields.name: Plank - Rotation
fields.description: The Plank - Rotation targets the core muscles, including the obliques and transverse abdominis. Start in a plank position, then rotate your torso to lift one arm towards the ceiling, keeping your hips stable. Avoid letting your hips sag or rise; maintain a straight line from head to heels.

fields.name: Plank - One-Arm
fields.description: The one-arm plank is a core exercise that targets the abs, obliques, and shoulders. Start in a standard plank position, then lift one arm straight in front of you, keeping your body aligned and hips level. Avoid twisting your hips or shoulders to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Plank - One-Leg
fields.description: The one-leg plank is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back while also engaging the glutes and shoulders. Start in a standard plank position, then lift one leg off the ground, keeping your hips level and core tight. Avoid letting your hips sag or rotate to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Plank - Stir the Pot
fields.description: The Plank - Stir the Pot is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Begin in a plank position with your forearms on a stability ball, then move your arms in a circular motion as if stirring a pot. Keep your hips stable to avoid swaying.

fields.name: Plank - Walk Out
fields.description: The Plank Walk Out targets the core, shoulders, and upper back. Start in a standing position, bend at the hips, and walk your hands forward into a plank position, then walk them back to stand. Avoid letting your hips sag as you walk out to maintain proper alignment.

fields.name: Plank - Contralateral
fields.description: The plank - contralateral is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Start in a standard plank position, then lift your right arm and left leg simultaneously, keeping your body stable. Avoid letting your hips sag or rotate; maintain a straight line from head to heels.

fields.name: Renegade Row
fields.description: The renegade row is a core exercise that also targets the back, shoulders, and arms. Start in a plank position with dumbbells in each hand, row one dumbbell to your hip while stabilizing your body. Avoid twisting your hips; keep them square to the ground for maximum core engagement.

fields.name: Renegade Row - DB
fields.description: The Renegade Row with dumbbells targets your core, back, and shoulders. Start in a plank position with a dumbbell in each hand, rowing one arm at a time while keeping your hips stable. Avoid letting your hips rotate; maintain a strong core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Plank - Copenhagen - Long Lever

fields.name: Low Ab Drill - Straight-Leg - Bilateral
fields.description: The Low Ab Drill - Straight-Leg - Bilateral targets the lower abdominal muscles by engaging the core. Lie on your back with legs extended straight, lift them slightly off the ground, and hold. Avoid arching your lower back by keeping your core tight throughout the exercise.

fields.name: Crunch - Supine
fields.description: The crunch - supine targets the core muscles, specifically the rectus abdominis. Lie on your back with knees bent, feet flat on the floor, and lift your shoulders off the ground using your core. Avoid pulling on your neck with your hands to prevent strain.

fields.name: Crunch - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Crunch on a Swiss Ball targets the core muscles, including the rectus abdominis and obliques. Sit on the ball, walk your feet forward, and lie back until your lower back is supported, then curl your torso up by engaging your core. Avoid pulling on your neck; focus on lifting with your abs.

fields.name: Crunch - Seated - High Pulley
fields.description: The seated high pulley crunch targets the core muscles, focusing on the upper and lower abdominals. Sit on a bench facing a high pulley machine, grasp the rope attachment, and crunch forward by contracting your abs. Avoid pulling with your arms; focus on using your core to drive the movement.

fields.name: Crunch - Incline - High Pulley
fields.description: The Incline High Pulley Crunch targets the core muscles, focusing on the upper abs. Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad, hold the pulley rope above your head, and crunch forward by engaging your core. Avoid pulling with your arms; focus on using your abs to drive the movement.

fields.name: Crunch - Kneeling - High Pulley
fields.description: The kneeling high pulley crunch targets the core muscles, focusing on the abdominals. Kneel facing a high pulley with a rope attachment, hold the ends by your ears, and crunch down by contracting your abs. Avoid pulling with your arms; focus on using your core to drive the movement.

fields.name: Crunch - Swiss Ball - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Crunch - Swiss Ball - Low Pulley targets the core muscles, focusing on the abdominals. Anchor your feet, lie back on the Swiss ball, and hold the pulley handle with both hands, crunching forward by engaging your core. Avoid pulling with your arms; let your abs do the work.

fields.name: Crunch - Pre-Stretch - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Crunch - Pre-Stretch on a Swiss Ball targets your core muscles, focusing on the abdominals. Begin by sitting on the ball, then walk your feet forward until your lower back is supported, and perform a crunch by lifting your shoulders towards the ceiling. Avoid pulling on your neck; instead, keep your chin slightly tucked and focus on engaging your core.

fields.name: Hip Raise - Supine
fields.description: The Hip Raise - Supine is a core exercise that primarily targets the abdominal muscles and lower back. Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat, then lift your hips towards the ceiling while squeezing your glutes. Avoid arching your lower back by keeping your core engaged throughout the movement.

fields.name: Sit-Up - Janda
fields.description: The Janda Sit-Up is a core exercise that targets the abdominal muscles while minimizing hip flexor involvement. To perform it, anchor your feet under a stable surface and focus on pulling your heels towards your glutes as you curl up. Avoid using momentum to lift your torso; instead, engage your abs throughout the movement.

fields.name: Knee Pull-In - Supine - Low Pulley
fields.description: The Knee Pull-In - Supine - Low Pulley is a core exercise that targets the abdominal muscles. Lie on your back with your feet hooked to a low pulley, then pull your knees towards your chest while keeping your lower back pressed against the floor. Avoid using momentum; focus on controlled movements for maximum effectiveness.

fields.name: Knee Pull-In - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Knee Pull-In on a Swiss Ball is a core exercise targeting the abdominals and hip flexors. Start in a plank position with your shins on the ball and pull your knees toward your chest, keeping your core engaged. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Knee Pull-In - Swiss Ball - Unilateral
fields.description: The Knee Pull-In on a Swiss Ball targets your core, focusing on the abs and obliques. Start in a plank position with your shins on the ball, then pull one knee towards your chest while maintaining balance. Avoid letting your hips sag to keep tension on your core.

fields.name: Jackknife - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Jackknife on a Swiss Ball is a core exercise that targets your abs, hip flexors, and stabilizing muscles. Begin in a plank position with your shins on the ball, then draw your knees toward your chest while keeping your back straight. Avoid letting your hips sag to maintain proper form.

fields.name: Jackknife - Swiss Ball - Unilateral
fields.description: The Jackknife on a Swiss Ball Unilateral targets the core, focusing on the abdominals and obliques. Begin in a plank position with your feet on the ball and draw one knee towards your chest while maintaining balance. Avoid letting your hips sag to ensure maximum core engagement.

fields.name: Garhammer Raise - Incline
fields.description: The Garhammer Raise - Incline is a core exercise that primarily targets the lower abs and obliques. Lie back on an incline bench, gripping the sides for support, and lift your knees towards your chest, focusing on engaging your core. Avoid swinging your legs for momentum to ensure maximum muscle engagement.

fields.name: Garhammer Raise - Hanging
fields.description: The Garhammer Raise - Hanging is a core exercise that primarily targets the lower abs. Hang from a pull-up bar with your legs straight, then lift your knees towards your chest while keeping your core engaged. Avoid swinging your body to maintain focus on the abs.

fields.name: Leg Raise - Flat
fields.description: The leg raise - flat is a core exercise that primarily targets the lower abdominal muscles. Lie flat on your back with your legs straight, then lift them towards the ceiling while keeping your lower back pressed into the ground. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Leg Raise - Incline
fields.description: The incline leg raise is a core exercise that primarily targets the lower abdominal muscles. Lie back on an incline bench, grip the handles, and lift your legs towards the ceiling while keeping them straight. Avoid arching your back by engaging your core throughout the movement.

fields.name: Leg Raise - Hanging
fields.description: The Hanging Leg Raise is a core exercise that primarily targets the lower abdominals and hip flexors. Keep your legs straight and lift them to waist height while engaging your core. Avoid swinging your body to maintain control and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Ab Roll-Out - Swiss Ball
fields.description: The Ab Roll-Out with a Swiss Ball is a core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Start on your knees with your forearms on the ball, then roll the ball forward by extending your arms while keeping your core engaged. Avoid arching your back by maintaining a straight line from your head to your knees.

fields.name: Ab Roll-Out - Kneeling
fields.description: The kneeling ab roll-out is a core exercise that primarily targets the abdominal muscles. Start on your knees with an ab wheel in front of you, then slowly roll forward while keeping your core engaged and back straight. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Ab Roll-Out - Standing
fields.description: The standing ab roll-out is a core exercise that targets the abs, obliques, and lower back. Start in a standing position with an ab wheel, engage your core, and roll the wheel forward while maintaining a straight line from head to heels. Avoid arching your back to prevent strain and maximize effectiveness.

fields.name: Dragon Flag
fields.description: The Dragon Flag is an advanced core exercise that targets the abdominals, obliques, and lower back. Keep your body straight and rigid as you lower and raise it, using your shoulders as the pivot point. Avoid arching your back to maintain proper form and prevent injury.
